{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "library-api-2024",
		"name": "Library Management API",
		"description": "Complete REST API for managing a library system with books, authors, members, and borrowings.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Import this collection\n2. Run **Auth > Register Librarian** to create admin user\n3. Token is auto-saved to `{{token}}` variable\n4. All other requests will use the saved token\n\n## Variables\n\nThis collection uses auto-saved variables:\n- `base_url`: API base URL (default: http://localhost:3001/api)\n- `token`: JWT authentication token\n- `user_id`: Last created/fetched user ID\n- `author_id`: Last created/fetched author ID\n- `category_id`: Last created/fetched category ID\n- `book_id`: Last created/fetched book ID\n- `borrowing_id`: Last created/fetched borrowing ID\n\nTest scripts automatically save IDs from responses for use in subsequent requests.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"auth": {
		"type": "bearer",
		"bearer": [
			{
				"key": "token",
				"value": "{{token}}",
				"type": "string"
			}
		]
	},
	"event": [
		{
			"listen": "prerequest",
			"script": {
				"type": "text/javascript",
				"exec": [
					"// Set base_url if not already set",
					"if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('base_url')) {",
					"    pm.collectionVariables.set('base_url', 'http://localhost:3001/api');",
					"}"
				]
			}
		}
	],
